description: "Update design tokens from Figma — supports Figma MCP (paste URL) or local file. Clones kit from GitHub, installs into app, writes tokens/design.tokens, runs generate:tokens."
globs: "tokens/**/*,scripts/generate-design-tokens.cjs,src/designSystem/generated/**/*"
alwaysApply: false
---

When the user says **Update design tokens from Figma** (or when working under `tokens/`, the generator script, or `src/designSystem/generated/`):

## Step 1 — Clone + install (terminal first; ask nothing yet)

```bash
cd "$(pwd)"
CACHE="${HOME}/.cache/CursorReactNativeAgents"

if [[ ! -f "$CACHE/design-token/install/run-update-design-tokens.sh" ]]; then
  git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/codeandtheory/CursorReactNativeAgents.git "$CACHE" \
    || git clone --depth 1 git@github.com:codeandtheory/CursorReactNativeAgents.git "$CACHE"
fi

bash "$CACHE/design-token/install/run-update-design-tokens.sh" "$(pwd)"
```

Then follow `.cursor/skills/design-tokens-kit/SKILL.md` from **Phase 2** (or `$HOME/.cache/CursorReactNativeAgents/design-token/.cursor/skills/design-tokens-kit/SKILL.md`).

## Step 2 — Choose token source (ask once)

Ask the user:

> "How would you like to provide the design tokens?
> **A)** Paste a Figma URL — I'll fetch variables directly from Figma via MCP.
> **B)** Provide a local file path to your exported `design.tokens` file."

**If A (Figma MCP):**
- Parse `fileKey` (segment after `/design/`) and `nodeId` (`node-id=` param, replace `-` with `:`).
- Call `get_variable_defs` via the Figma MCP.
- Map the result to the `Theme Dark` / `Theme Light` JS-like format and write `tokens/design.tokens` directly.
- If MCP fails or is rate-limited, fall back to option B.

**If B (local file):**
- `mkdir -p tokens && cp "<user-path>" tokens/design.tokens`
- Or confirm `tokens/design.tokens` already exists.

## Step 3 — Codegen

```bash
npm run generate:tokens
```

On semantic validation errors, edit **only** `tokens/semantic-colors.json`, then re-run (max 3 times).

Do not hand-edit `src/designSystem/generated/*.ts`.
